    <text>
    <body>
        <p>Virginia-born housejoiner and assessor. Lived with Congressman Aaron Harding in Green County, Kentucky in 1860. Served as a tax assessor of the 2nd Tax District of Kentucky from 1863 to 1866.</p>

    </body>
